When custom event is initiated by either of the first two constructors listed in IssueEvent API: https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/6.4.1/com/atlassian/jira/event/issue/IssueEvent.html
(meaning that no event Comment or changeGroup is set)
Then ServiceDesk SLA timer logic treats such event invariably as ISSUE_CREATED, and if SLA is configured to start timer on "Issue Created", then such events cause unwanted triggering of the timer.
It took many hours to get to the root of this problem. Workaround was to use different IssueEvent constructor.
Deep debugging revealed the root cause being here: 
{code}
com.atlassian.servicedesk.internal.sla.condition.factory.ConditionHelper{
...
  protected boolean hasIssueJustBeenCreated(IssueEvent event) {
    return event.getChangeLog() == null && event.getComment() == null;
  }
...
}
{code}

